      <h1 class='title'>Anti-terrorism, Crime and Security Act 2001: Part 4 Powers</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='lords-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 22 February 2005 vol 669 cc55-6WS</cite>
      
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_55ws' title='Col. 55WS &mdash; HL Deb 22 February 2005 vol 669 c55WS' name='column_55ws' href='#column_55ws' rel='bookmark'>55WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0669P0-04867'>
        <a name='S5LV0669P0_20050222_LWS_9'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-patricia-scotland' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0669P0_20050222_LWS_9' title='Link to this speech by Ms Patricia Scotland' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-patricia-scotland" title="Ms Patricia Scotland">The Minister of State, Home Office (Baroness Scotland of Asthal)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S5LV0669P0-04867">The Lord Carlile of Berriew QC has completed the report on the operation of Part 4 of the <a href="/acts/anti-terrorism-crime-and-security-act-2001">Anti-Terrorism, Crime and Security Act 2001</a>, in 2004, which will be laid before the House today. This is an important function. Lord Carlile exercises independent scrutiny over the operation of Part 4 in recognition of the exceptional and sensitive nature of these powers.</p><a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_56ws' title='Col. 56WS &mdash; HL Deb 22 February 2005 vol 669 c56WS' name='column_56ws' href='#column_56ws' rel='bookmark'>56WS</a><p id="S5LV0669P0-04868">We are grateful to Lord Carlile for his work and I am sure that this view will be widely shared.</p><p id="S5LV0669P0-04869">We are pleased to note that he is again satisfied that certifications have been made only in appropriate cases. He has also made a number of other helpful recommendations which will provide a useful contribution to the debates on Part 4 and the proposed alternatives.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
